steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"a2o44","text":"Plate cells on 6-well plate on SNL a day before transfection (number of cells shown in the table below).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4839f","text":"A day after transfection cells were passaged from 6-well plate into 10cm Petri dishes with SNL. Cells from each well were split into 3 Petri dishes in 3 different densities (1/2, 1/3 and 1/5 of the cells).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8uv6v","text":"24 hours later apply puromycin selection (at the adequate concentration for your cell line of interest) for 48hours to select for cells that contain the Cas9 plasmid (there is no selection in the targeting vector!).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6hlun","text":"After 48 hours of puromycin selection feed cells with regular ES medium every day until ready to pick colonies (usually 12-14 days after transfection).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3noag","text":"pick colonies (usually 12-14 days after transfection).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a02ci","text":"follow ES cell picking protocol","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
